==Details==
{{Quest details page|Making Friends with My Arm}}

==Walkthrough==
===Starting out===
''Items required: None.''<br/>
''Items recommended: [[Weight-reducing clothing]] and [[stamina potion]]s, a teleport to [[Draynor Village]], Dramen or Lunar Staff, food for next part unless banking.''
{{Checklist|
*Talk to [[Burntmeat]] located in the troll stronghold kitchen (stairs to the south after entering).{{Chat option|2Yes, I'll take your quest.|2Okay.}}, or {{Chat option|1Carry on|2Yes, I'll take your quest.|2Okay.}} if boosts are being used.
*Talk to [[My Arm]] located by the herb patch on the roof of the troll stronghold (ladder up to the west or agility shortcut.{{Chat option|2I'm doing another quest for Burntmeat.|2Wolfbone said we should go by sea.}}
*Talk to [[Larry]] (Fairy ring code {{fairycode|dks}} then run to the transportation symbol on the coast to the north, east of [[Rellekka]]){{Chat option|2Could I transport My Arm in your boat?|1My Arm is a troll.}}, or {{Chat option|3Can I transport My Arm in your boat?|2My Arm is a troll.}} if you no longer have the [[clockwork book]]
*Talk to Larry again.{{Chat option|2Can I transport My Arm in your boat?}}, or {{Chat option|3Can I transport My Arm in your boat?}} if you no longer have the [[clockwork book]]
*Board the boat.
}}
===Troll Diplomacy===
''Items required: Any [[pickaxe]] and [[rope]] (both obtainable during this part), mining and agility level boost (if necessary).''<br/>''Items recommended: [[Weight-reducing clothing]] and [[stamina potion]]s, a teleport to [[Draynor Village]] (at least 2 teleport uses, like a charged [[Glory]] Amulet (2) ), food for failing obstacles.''
[[File:Weiss Safespot 1.png|thumb|Safe spot halfway through the thrower troll section.]]
{{Checklist|If you did not bring a rope, search the wrecked boat for one. Take a pickaxe too as you'll need it later.
*Attempt to mine the cave entrance '''(do not use your boost yet if you brought one)'''
*Climb up the rockslides nearby (boosting to 68 agility if necessary), and use a rope on the tree.
*Climb the rope and cross the ledge.
*Climb the last rockslide and pass the fallen tree.
*Talk to [[Boulder]]. {{Chat option|2Wolfbone's sent My Arm from the Troll Stronghold.|3I'll be back!}}
*Sneak in via the broken fence just east. Prepare to run past a lot of angry trolls.
*Go south along the city's edge, then west. Once you reach a small alleyway to the north (see image), recover your run energy if necessary.
*Run to the bucket spawn and stand there for a moment.
*Click on the 'little boulder' just north of you, and right before reaching it, click on the hole all the way to the north to climb down.
*Once descended, quickly go south and pass through the narrow gap. '''DO NOT''' climb up the ramp.
** This acts as a checkpoint once knocked out upon re-entering the gap in the fence.
** <i>Note: If you stop moving before the checkpoint, the trolls will catch you and you will spawn outside of the city</i>.
*Empty your hands and swim further into the cave while avoiding the first set of trolls' stones.
*For the second set of trolls, the final troll will throw rocks, creating stepping stones. When the troll begins throwing, move one tile forward, making a path of 5 stones to the edge of the water. Click one tile toward the cave exit as soon as the throwing animation starts until the path is finished.
**If you fail, you will be sent back to just before the second set of trolls.
*Mine the cave exit (boosting to 72 mining if necessary).
*Talk to [[Mother]].{{Chat option|3Let's move on with the chat.}}
*After [[Snowflake]] leaves, pick all possible options.{{Chat option|1Tell him goutweed is delicious.|1Tell him how tough Stronghold trolls are.|1Tell him to show respect to his daughter.|1Tell him you love his daughter!}}
*Talk to My Arm.{{Chat option|1Mother wasn't very nice to Snowflake in there.|1Snowflake, you seemed to like My Arm.|2Odd Mushroom, why are you here with us?|4Does Mother respect anything except fighting?|2I did some fishing and fetched some stuff.}}
}}

===The Wise "Dead" Man===
*''Items required: [[Hammer]], [[Saw]], 5 [[Mahogany plank]]s, [[Bolt of cloth]], [[Cadava berries]]''
*''Recommended items: [[Varrock]] teleport
{{Checklist|
*Talk to the [[Wise Old Man]] in [[Draynor Village]].{{Chat option|1Ask about My Arm.|2Can you pretend you're dead?|2You owe me a favour after the Fishing Colony quest.}}
*Build the coffin next to the Wise Old Man.
*Speak to the [[Apothecary]] in [[Varrock]].
**Chat options depend on the quests the player has completed. Pick "Talk about Making Friends with My Arm."
*Talk to Wise Old Man back in Draynor Village.{{Chat option|1Ask about My Arm.}}
*Take the [[Old man's coffin]].
}}

===Matricide===
''Items required: Combat equipment (preferably ranged), food and potions as they can hit through prayer, Old man's coffin''

{{Instance}}
{{Checklist|
*Return to Weiss by travelling with Larry's boat.
*Go through the cave entrance.
*Talk to My Arm by the north entrance.
*Talk to [[Odd Mushroom]].{{Chat option|1I'll never leave you.}}
*Talk to Snowflake.{{Chat option|1So I can't teleport, and I may lose stuff? Okay.}}
*Fight [[Don't Know What]]. Use protect from range and damage him with melee or range.
*Fight [[Mother]]. Activate protect from range. Grab a bucket from the pile and use it on the large barrel of water. Then use the bucket of water on the Fire of Domination to extinguish it, which then makes your attacks effective. Mother will stun the player and drain some prayer points if able to get into melee range, therefore it's preferred if you fought back with Ranged while running from Mother. He can also be safespotted by trapping him to the East of the staircase and standing immediately South of the stairs in the Western-most square.
}}

===A New Leader===
''Items required: [[Bucket]]''
{{Checklist|
*Talk to My Arm.
*Talk to Wise Old Man, and then Snowflake.{{Chat option|1What do you want with goat dung?}}
*Pick up [[goat poo]] in the north-east building to get [[goat dung]]. (Buckets of water can be found in the building and emptied)
*Talk to Snowflake.
*Read the [[Weiss fire notes]] Snowflake gives you.
*Talk to Snowflake.
}}

